#Text=The Cleveland Cavaliers ( 24 - 9 ) defeated the Washington Wizards ( 15 - 18 ) 121 - 115 on Wednesday .
#Text=Kyrie Irving has progressively improved since returning from the fractured kneecap he suffered in last season 's Finals versus the Warriors .

#Text=He 's increased his playing time over the seven games he 's played to date , and had gotten up to almost a full allotment , 29 minutes , in the Cavs ' most recent contest versus the Raptors on Monday .
#Text=The stage appeared set for the All-Star point guard to receive a regular share of minutes Wednesday , and Irving certainly did n't disappoint .
#Text=He poured in 34 points , 19 of which came in an explosive final period , to lead Cleveland to a high - scoring victory .

#Text=He also complemented the scoring with five rebounds , three assists , a pair of steals and a block , all over a robust 34 minutes that provided unequivocable proof that Irving is back at full strength and ready to contribute to a Cavs championship push .
#Text=Despite his impressive performance , Irving was not the team - high scorer on the night .
#Text=That honor unsurprisingly fell to LeBron James , who posted a monster 34 - point , 10 - rebound double - double .
#Text=He added four assists , a steal and a block for good measure .
#Text=J.R.
#Text=Smith was a prolific third scoring wheel , pitching in with 25 points , three rebounds , an assist and three steals , his second straight 20 - point - plus performance .
#Text=The effort included five three - pointers in 10 attempts , giving Smith an impressive 13 baskets from beyond the arc over the last two contests .

#Text=Tristan Thompson continued his stretch of solid play at the center position , posting 12 points , three rebounds and an assist , while Kevin Love pitched in with eight points , nine rebounds , a pair of steals and a block .
#Text=The Cavaliers improved to 24 - 9 and remain atop the Eastern Conference 's Central Division .
#Text=They head to Minnesota to take on the Timberwolves on Friday .
#Text=The home team received solid efforts from all five starters , and would have likely prevailed if they 'd been up against almost any other team on Wednesday .
#Text=They shot an outstanding 55 percent from the field , and a particularly stellar 58 from long range .
#Text=The Wizards were led by Garrett Temple 's 21 points .
#Text=After five straight sub - par scoring efforts , it was Temple 's first 20 - point - plus performance since Dec. 23 versus the Grizzlies .
#Text=John Wall churned out yet another double double , tallying 20 points ( including a perfect 4 for 4 from beyond the arc ) and dishing out 12 assists .
#Text=Meanwhile , Jared Dudley , Otto Porter , Jr. and Marcin Gortat all managed 12 - point efforts , and contributed solid shares of rebounds , assists and steals as well .
#Text=Gary Neal paced the Washington reserves with 13 points , a rebound and an assist .
#Text=The Wizards fell to 15 - 18 and remain in last place in the Eastern Conference 's Southeast Division .
#Text=They 'll be at home again on Friday to take on the Toronto Raptors .
